  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">The horizon-radius of a <math altimg="si41.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> -dimensional Schwarzschild black hole of mass M is given by [11] <math altimg="si57.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mn>16</mn><mi>π</mi><mi>M</mi><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><msub><mrow><mover accent="true"><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">ˆ</mo></mrow></mover></mrow><mrow><mi>D</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></msup></math>, where <math altimg="si58.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mover accent="true"><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">ˆ</mo></mrow></mover></mrow><mrow><mi>D</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mrow><mi>π</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>D</mi><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Γ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> is the generalized area of a unit <math altimg="si59.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> -sphere</subfield>
